kelly fenson hood jenna davis phd search search this site stanford university jenna davis phd assistant professor dept of civil and environmental engineering higgins magid fellow woods institute for the environment kelly fenson hood navigation research meet the poop group cv & press teaching w&s resources w&s scholarships & fellowships contact home meet the poop group kelly fenson hood kelly is the group research manager for the davis research group ie the poop group she joined the team in october of 2011 her area of interest is in behavior change with a focus on health and hygiene kelly has an ma in health and development communication from the university of denver du and a ba in international health education from the university of colorado denver she worked with du for three years on an urban slum behavior change campaign in nairobi kenya the campaign focused on increasing hand washing behaviors and point of use water treatment prior to that kelly worked in the health promotion department at du concentrating on college health issues including hand washing and tobacco policy in this position she passed one of the first campus wide smoke free tobacco policies in colorado last modified fri 9 mar 2012 at 15 12 login stanford university all rights reserved stanford ca 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
